{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Privacy Policy{% endblock %}

{% block body %}

	<!-- Title page -->
	<section class="bg-img1 txt-center p-lr-15 p-tb-92" style="background-image: url('{{ asset('assets/images/privacy.jpg') }}');">
		<h2 class="ltext-105 cl0 txt-center">
			Read our Privacy Policy
		</h2>
	</section>	
    <section class="bg0 p-t-104 p-b-116">
		<div class="container">
			   <div class="grid">
        <article class="card px-5 py-5 mb-5" aria-labelledby="privacy-title">
          <h2 id="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h2>

          <section id="general" aria-labelledby="general-title">
            <h3 id="general-title">1. General Information</h3>
            <p>At <strong>Optiview</strong>, protecting your personal data is a top priority. This document is a demonstrative privacy policy prepared for an academic project (PFE) and is not legal advice. It describes typical processing activities and safeguards an e-commerce site would communicate to users.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="controller" aria-labelledby="controller-title">
            <h3 id="controller-title">2. Data Controller</h3>
            <p><strong>Optiview – E-Commerce Platform</strong><br>
            Email: <a href="mailto:contact@optiview.com">contact@optiview.com</a><br>
            Website: <a href="https://www.optiview.com">www.optiview.com</a></p>
          </section>

          <section id="collection" aria-labelledby="collection-title">
            <h3 id="collection-title">3. Collection &amp; Processing of Personal Data</h3>
            <p>We collect personal data only when you voluntarily provide it during registration, ordering, or contacting us. Typical data elements include:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Full name</li>
              <li>Postal address</li>
              <li>Email address</li>
              <li>Phone number</li>
              <li>Payment information (processed by third-party providers)</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="purpose" aria-labelledby="purpose-title">
            <h3 id="purpose-title">4. Purpose of Data Processing</h3>
            <p>We use personal data for limited, explicit purposes:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Processing and fulfilling orders</li>
              <li>Arranging deliveries</li>
              <li>Providing customer support</li>
              <li>Sending order confirmations and service-related messages</li>
              <li>Optional: Marketing communications if you opted in</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="thirdparties" aria-labelledby="thirdparties-title">
            <h3 id="thirdparties-title">5. Sharing Data with Third Parties</h3>
            <p>We share data with trusted third parties only when necessary to fulfill a contract or deliver a service, for example:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Shipping and logistics providers</li>
              <li>Payment processors (PCI-compliant)</li>
              <li>Analytics &amp; hosting providers</li>
            </ul>
            <p>All third parties are selected with care and are expected to implement appropriate data protection measures.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="security" aria-labelledby="security-title">
            <h3 id="security-title">6. Data Security</h3>
            <p>We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against unauthorized access, loss, or alteration. Examples include encrypted connections (HTTPS), restricted access controls, and secure backups.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="cookies" aria-labelledby="cookies-title">
            <h3 id="cookies-title">7. Cookies</h3>
            <p>Our website uses cookies and similar technologies to enhance usability, enable shopping-cart functionality, and provide analytics. You can manage or disable cookies via your browser settings. Note that disabling certain cookies may affect core functionality.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="rights" aria-labelledby="rights-title">
            <h3 id="rights-title">8. Your Rights</h3>
            <p>You have rights regarding your personal data, including:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Right to access the data we hold about you</li>
              <li>Right to request correction or deletion</li>
              <li>Right to withdraw consent for specific processing</li>
              <li>Right to lodge a complaint with a data protection authority</li>
            </ul>
            <p>For requests, contact: <a href="mailto:privacy@optiview.com">privacy@optiview.com</a></p>
          </section>

          <section id="changes" aria-labelledby="changes-title">
            <h3 id="changes-title">9. Changes to this Policy</h3>
            <p>We may update this policy to reflect legal requirements or service changes. Material changes will be communicated on our website.</p>
          </section>

        </article>

        <aside class="card px-5 py-5 mb-5" aria-labelledby="access-title">
          <h2 id="access-title">Accessibility Statement</h2>

          <section id="commitment" aria-labelledby="commitment-title">
            <h3 id="commitment-title">Commitment to Accessibility</h3>
            <p>Optiview is committed to making our platform accessible to all users, including people with disabilities. This statement outlines our goals and the measures we take to improve accessibility.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="measures" aria-labelledby="measures-title">
            <h3 id="measures-title">Measures Taken</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Semantic HTML and logical heading structure</li>
              <li>Keyboard-navigable menus and controls</li>
              <li>Alternative (alt) text for product images</li>
              <li>High-contrast text and scalable fonts</li>
              <li>Compatibility with common screen readers</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="standards" aria-labelledby="standards-title">
            <h3 id="standards-title">Standards</h3>
            <p>We aim to follow recognized accessibility guidelines such as <code>WCAG 2.1</code> (level AA) where feasible for this project.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="feedback" aria-labelledby="feedback-title">
            <h3 id="feedback-title">Feedback &amp; Assistance</h3>
            <p>If you encounter barriers while using our website, please contact us so we can provide assistance or an alternative format:</p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:accessibility@optiview.com">accessibility@optiview.com</a></p>
            <p>Typical response time (project demo): 2 business days.</p>
          </section>

        </aside>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top:18px" class="card px-5 py-5 mb-5">
        <h2 class="contact">Quick Contact &amp; Notes</h2>
        <p>For further enquiries regarding this demonstrative policy, contact our data team:</p>
        <p>
          Privacy: <a href="mailto:privacy@optiview.com">privacy@optiview.com</a><br>
          Accessibility: <a href="mailto:accessibility@optiview.com">accessibility@optiview.com</a>
        </p>
       
      </div>
			
		</div>
	</section>	
 
 
{% endblock %}
